<div class="mt-16 space-y-12">
  <!-- How to Use Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">How to Use the Pose Progress Tracker</h2>
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-primary max-w-none">
      <p class="lead">Track your yoga journey by documenting your progress in specific poses. The Pose Progress Tracker helps you monitor improvements in flexibility, strength, and alignment.</p>
      
      <h3>Getting Started</h3>
      <ol class="space-y-3">
        <li>Enter the name of the pose you want to track</li>
        <li>Rate your current progress on a scale of 1-10</li>
        <li>Record your maximum hold time in seconds</li>
        <li>Evaluate your alignment quality</li>
        <li>Add notes about sensations or challenges</li>
        <li>Optionally upload a photo for visual reference</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tips Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Making the Most of Your Tracker</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Progress Tips</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li>• Track poses consistently (weekly/bi-weekly)</li>
          <li>• Focus on quality over quantity</li>
          <li>• Note specific improvements</li>
          <li>• Document any modifications used</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">Photo Tips</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
          <li>• Use consistent lighting</li>
          <li>• Capture the same angle</li>
          <li>• Wear fitted clothing</li>
          <li>• Include full pose alignment</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">How often should I track my progress?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">We recommend tracking each pose weekly or bi-weekly to observe meaningful changes while maintaining consistent practice.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">What should I include in my notes?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Document sensations, challenges, breakthroughs, and any modifications you used. This information helps identify patterns in your practice.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Are progress photos necessary?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">While optional, photos provide valuable visual feedback on your alignment and progress over time.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Can I track multiple poses?</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Yes! Create separate entries for each pose you want to track. We recommend focusing on 3-5 poses at a time for best results.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>